  "texts": [
    "This limitation motivates our proposed Dual Transformer architecture, which introduces a two-stage framework: the first Transformer encodes sentiment signals from multiple related companies, and the second integrates this encoded sentiment with historical price data to forecast the target company's stock price.By decoupling sentiment modeling and price forecasting, the Dual Transformer enables more effective integration of external sentiment influences.",
    "This structure differs from existing approaches by explicitly modeling cross-company sentiment interactions, a dimension often ignored in previous Transformer-based financial models.",
    "Therefore, our work not only applies Transformer architecture to stock prediction but also extends its capability to capture multi-entity relationships, offering both methodological and empirical advancements.This paper aims to explore whether the news sentiment of related companies can improve the prediction of the stock price of a target company with the proposed Dual Transformer model.",
    "The main contributions of this research are:1.",
    "We propose a framework by incorporating news sentiment of related companies in stock price prediction and demonstrate that news sentiment of related companies offer predictive value for the target company's stock price movement when using the proposed model. 2."
  ],
